Section-themed inner pages (article/product/brand/compare/legal/about) + deeper SEO

Why: every inner page previously used the same hero + content shell, so the ~50
generated pages looked indistinguishable from each other. This refresh makes each
section visually distinct and strengthens the SEO/structured-data baseline at
the same time.

Layout / design (scripts/lib/site-shell.js, assets/css/main.css v16)
  - body[data-section] theme: per-section accent color, hero gradient, ornament,
    eyebrow pill with inline SVG icon, accent for H2/links/cards.
  - Pill-style breadcrumb bar on every inner page.
  - Page-hero gains eyebrow tag, H1, lead, meta row (author / published / updated /
    reading time) and optional hero stat chips on hubs.
  - Article prose: drop cap, accent H2 rail, themed blockquote, hr divider.
  - Print styles hide nav/footer/CTAs; legal section gets paper-white body.

SEO
  - Combined @graph JSON-LD on every inner page: Organization + WebSite +
    BreadcrumbList + page-specific node (WebPage / Article / CollectionPage /
    ItemList / AboutPage), with absolute URLs in the breadcrumb.
  - Article pages emit og:type=article, article:published_time / modified_time /
    author / section, full Article schema (wordCount, timeRequired, author,
    publisher, image) and reading time computed from the body fragment.
  - Per-page keywords on every generated page (hand-mapped for each article slug
    and product/brand/compare/legal/about page).
  - Stronger meta baseline: hreflang (en + x-default), max-image-preview:large,
    color-scheme, referrer, X-Content-Type-Options, format-detection.
  - Sitemap: lastmod added to every entry; dropped stale #-fragment URLs.
  - robots.txt: explicit allow for GPTBot / ClaudeBot / Google-Extended,
    Disallow /content/, declared Host.
  - Home index.html: bumped asset cache to v=16.

Regenerated 47 generated HTML files via generate-site.js + generate-articles.js.
